# migrated from tests/cases/logic_no_overlap.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test logic_no_overlap]
# gen249: an explicit "no X are Y" premise rules out being both, even when a
# "some" premise appears elsewhere.
> If all Zorks are Morks, some Morks are Borks, and no Borks are Zorks, can a Bork also be a Zork? Explain your reasoning.
< No -- the statement says those classes do not overlap.

